[8] gridDescription: To the South is a path.
[9] look: The renowned scientist - Rufus Digby - is standing by a large computer system. His assistant Dr. Tanaka is using a complex machine in the corner.
[15] deeperLook: coffee_You feel a little more alert.:chemical_You decide it's unwise to go near the hazardous chemicals.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is Rifton Cave. To the South is the Weapons Shop.
[9] look: Two local miners - Guto and Bart - are sitting at a table covered by a complicated geological atlas and talking to each other.
[15] deeperLook: atlas_The atlas shows the geology of the local area. From the key you can see that the island Rifton is situated on is formed from a mixture of sandstone and limestone with an intrusion of igneous rock underneath Rifton caves and another on Rifton beach.

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a path.
[9] look: Inside the library is a maze of books - some which cover topics you have studied and others with seemingly indecipherable names. There are several people reading who don't look like they wish to be disturbed. A receptionist is sitting at the front desk typing at the computer.:Inside the library is a maze of books. Walls are hidden behind endless tomes. An elderly man with a straw hat is reading a book about fertilser and its effects on crop yield. A woman with dark hair tied in a blue headscarf is reading a guidebook to Mesetra - a city far in the East. A man with oiled hair and wearing a suit is reading a complex book on biology.:Inside the library is a maze of books. Walls are hidden behind endless tomes. An elderly man with a straw hat is reading a book about fertilser and its effects on crop yield. A woman with dark hair tied in a blue headscarf is reading a guidebook to Mesetra - a city far in the East.:Inside the library is a maze of books. Walls are hidden behind endless tomes. A woman with dark hair tied in a blue headscarf is reading a guidebook to Mesetra - a city far in the East.:Inside the library is a maze of books. Walls are hidden behind endless tomes. An elderly man with a straw hat is reading a book about fertilser and its effects on crop yield.:Inside the library is a maze of books. Walls are hidden behind endless tomes. A woman with dark hair tied in a blue headscarf is reading a guidebook to Mesetra - a city far in the East. A man with oiled hair and wearing a suit is reading a complex book on biology.
[11] regexSecondLevelLook: browse books:books:look at books:view books:book:browse shelves:shelves
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: You take a look at the books in the 'Most-Popular' section.
[13] secondLevelLookGridItems: history of rifton village:the polluted lands:soil quality and gardening

[8] gridDescription: To the North is the Lab. To the West is the Library. To the East is a small cottage. To the South is a cobbled path.
[9] look: You seem to be at the highest point in the village - aside from the canyon walls towering above you to your north. When you look directly south you can see the cliff walls decline and merge with the lowlands. Far in the distance you can just about see a glimpse of the ocean.
[15] deeperLook: canyon_Stratified rock extends towards the ocean on both sides of the canyon.:ocean_What a lovely shade of blue.:lowlands_You can see a forest and further down is a beach.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a path. To the South is Dr Tanaka's house.
[9] look: Your computer is flashing with biological research. The walls are lined with shelves of books from your studies. Your room-mate - Vanya - is reading a newspaper at the kitchen table.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: You browse through your collection to see if there might be anything useful.
[15] deeperLook: shelves_Dozens of books on biology and natural science are organised neatly - just as you left them.:newspaper_The newspaper is open on an article about the energy market. The headline reads 'Is BioFuel the future of Terethia's energy needs?'

[8] gridDescription: To the South is a path.
[9] look: Inside the shop the wooden walls are covered with weapons in all shapes and sizes. Some look purely ornamental while others look potentially lethal. A young woman is polishing a blade behind a counter towards the back of the shop. [To buy an item type 'take' and then the item]
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: A wooden rack is situated near the door.
[15] deeperLook: wall_A selection of ornamental weapons from the Thian era with their distinctive red lacquered hilts is on display in the centre of the shop.:blade_It's so shiny!

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a path. To the East is Dr.Tanaka's House. To the South is the Town Square.
[9] look: The cottage looks old and has a thatched roof. An apple tree is growing by the front entrance. The cottage overlooks Rifton lake to the west - which extends out towards a cliff face in the distance. The door to the cottage does not appear to be locked.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: You open the door. Inside is a quaintly decorated room. Photographs of Rifton and various people from decades ago cover the walls. An elderly woman is knitting in a corner.
[15] deeperLook: cat_You look around the corner and see a fairly large cat lounging in the sunlight:stroke_You stroke the cat which rolls over onto its back and purrs:outside_You walk outside the cottage.:tree_It's the sort of tree you would have loved to have climbed as a child.:lake_The lake looks so calm. This must be why the cottage is situated here.:cliff_The village is surrounded by steep Sandstone cliffs that make up the canyon.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is your house. To the West is a small cottage. To the South is an allotment.
[9] look: The house is painted pale terracotta and is surrounded by small shrubs. The front door is locked.
[15] deeperLook: yellow flowers_The flowers are unlike those grown locally. Someone must have spent a lot of time caring for them.:shrub_Ouch! It's prickly.

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a path.
[9] look: The shop is quite small and sells groceries and clothes. A shopkeeper is chatting with a customer near the till. [To buy an item type 'take' and then the item]
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: The shop has a few items which look they could be useful.
[15] deeperLook: customer_One customer is flirting fairly obviously with the shopkeeper who seems to be enjoying it.:till_A voice of reason tells you to stay away from this.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a Weapons Shop. To the West is a local shop. To the East is a Bridge.
[9] look: To your south you can see the canyon drop off steeply towards the sea. There is a forest sloping down as the landscape shallows.

[5] cellName: on top of a wooden bridge
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a path. To the East is a path.
[9] look: The bridge is surrounded by bushes with twigs littering the ground. The view to the north is of the lake that Rifton is built around. A waterfall falls from over the top of the canyon in the distance. To the south the lake continues before it reaches another waterfall descending through Rifton forest.
[15] deeperLook: bridge_The bridge is made from wooden planks and is beginning to rot in places along the railings.:twig_You throw a twig into the water over the northern side of the bridge then turn to watch it float past on the southern side. You watch it fall over the waterfall further south:bushes_They look very prickly.:bush_They look very prickly.:jump_You feel a sudden urge to jump in the lake and ... *splash!* ... well now you're all wet.:lake_The lake looks enticingly cool:waterfall_You are on a plateau between two waterfalls - one to the north and one to the south. Is that something behind the waterfall to the north?:canyon_Stratified rock extends towards the ocean on both sides of the canyon.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a Bridge. To the East is the Town Square. To the South is the West Park.
[9] look: Small houses and fences create the alley either side of you.
[15] deeperLook: house_There are rows of quaint cottages that look like they were built a long time ago.:alley_The alley is narrow and littered with leaves. Two streetlamps stand unlit either side of you.:streetlamp_The lamps need to be lit manually - someone must light them every evening.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a path. To the East is an allotment. To the West is a path. To the South is the East Park.
[9] look: You are standing in a paved courtyard surrounded by houses and green spaces. A small fountain is in the centre of the paved area. A young man and woman are sitting on a bench next to it.
[15] deeperLook: fountain_The fountain appears to be solar powered. There are several coins in the basin.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is Dr Tanaka's House. To the West is the Town Square.
[9] look: There are several plots of land that look like plants grew on them once.
[15] deeperLook: plot_There are several plots of soil with numbered signs in front. It looks like most people in the village use this allotment

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a path. To the East is the East Park.
[9] look: A wooden hut is set up underneath the shade of a tree. A drinks vendor is standing inside preparing drinks.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is the Town Square. To the West is the West Park. To the South is a Viewpoint.
[9] look: This side of the park is covered with large trees - creating a leafy canopy overhead that casts a green light on the area. One of the trees looks like it would be easy to climb if you were so inclined.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: Just below the upper leaves of the tree you see a precariously-placed treehouse.
[15] deeperLook: climb tree_You walk over to the tree and begin climbing up the base of it. You feel a sense of adventure rush through you. Could you reach that branch just above you?:branch_You made it! You're already so high above the ground but you think you could make it above the canopy if you could just reach that protruding piece of bark...:reach_You made it! You're already so high above the ground but you think you could make it above the canopy if you could just reach that protruding piece of bark...:bark_You use the bark to grab on to and pull yourself up through the leaves of the canopy. You feel a sudden rush of wind past your face as you emerge above the trees. The view from this point is incredible; the canyon walls either side of you and the waterfall to your north and the ocean to the south and... a treehouse next to you?:treehouse_Just below the upper leaves of the tree you see a precariously-placed treehouse. You look inside and on a small table is a key and a piece of paper.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is the East Park. To the South is Rifton Forest.
[9] look: From here you have a far-reaching view south across the canyon and out to the ocean.

[5] cellName: at the edge of the forest overlooking Rifton Canyon.
[8] gridDescription: To the East is the Rifton entrance to the forest. To the South is a forested downward slope.
[9] look: The trees thin out towards the edge of the cliff - which drops steeply into the canyon. A massive waterfall is descending into the canyon from Rifton Village. As the sun moves in and out of the clouds a rainbow forms over the top of the waterfall.
[15] deeperLook: canyon_Rifton Canyon forms the picturesque geology that Rifton Village is built on:rainbow_You can see... a double rainbow?!:cliff_If you knew a lot about rock-climbing you'd probably have an urge to climb this steep cliff right now.:waterfall_There is a thunderous roar from the water cascading into the canyon below.:village_Rifton Village - your home - is situated to the North of the forest you are in. It is surrounded by the walls of the canyon.:trees_You can hear birds in the trees behind you.

[5] cellName: at the Rifton entrance to the forest.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is Rifton village. To the West is the edge of the forest overlooking the canyon. To the East is grassy knoll overgrown with moss. To the South is a deep thicket.
[9] look: To the south is a dense forest of desiduous trees. You know that you are on a mission but the nature-lover inside you wants to stop and look at all the wildlife!

[5] cellName: in a grassy knoll overgrown with moss.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is the Rifton entrance to the forest. To the East is a corner of the forest surrounded by canyon walls. To the South is a bramble patch.
[9] look: Above you to the north is a cliff face. At the top you can see the edge of Rifton village.

[5] cellName: in a corner of the forest surrounded by canyon walls.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a grassy knoll overgrown with moss.
[9] look: You are standing on the edge of a cliff that juts out over a large canyon to your east.
[15] deeperLook: canyon_There is a steep drop down to the rocks below. The canyon separates the plateau you are standing on from the main cliff face that makes up the walls surrounding Rifton.:cliff_You throw a pebble off the side of the cliff... you don't hear it hit the ground below.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is the edge of the forest overlooking Rifton Canyon. To the East is a deep thicket. To the South is a slope leading to the edge of the canyon.
[9] look: The trees thin out towards the edge of the cliff - which drops steeply into the canyon. The sound of the waterfall falling down from Rifton village is fairly deafening.
[15] deeperLook: waterfall_There is a thunderous roar from the water cascading into the canyon below

[8] gridDescription: To the North is the Rifton entrance to the forest. To the West is a forested downward slope. To the East is a path through brambles. To the South is a path through moss-covered rocks.
[9] look: You are in the densest section of the forest. You look up and can barely see the sky for the canopy overgrowth.
[15] deeperLook: canopy_You watch for a while and see several birds fly overhead. You can hear the sounds of other species nearby too.:birds_You can hear the sound of doves in the distance and noticed blackbirds flying nearby.

[5] cellName: walking along a path through brambles.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a grassy knoll overgrown with moss. To the West is a deep thicket. To the South is a grassy clearing.
[9] look: You are surrounded by shrubs and bushes that are covered in small berries.
[15] deeperLook: shrub_Ouch!:shrubs_Ouch!:bush_Ouch!:bushes_Ouch!:berry_There is a mixture of blackberry and loganberry bushes.:berries_There is a mixture of blackberry and loganberry bushes.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a clearing with a river running through. To the East is a slope leading to the edge of the canyon.
[9] look: The edge of the clearing is heavily covered with ivy and small bushes. Just visible - you can see the side of a crate underneath the foliage.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: You pull the crate out from the plants and open it.

[5] cellName: in a clearing next to a pool.
[8] gridDescription: To the East is a deeply overgrown canopy.
[9] look: The pool is still and is covered with a green algae. Small dragonflies are drifting over the surface.
[15] deeperLook: algae_The algae is a luminous green colour and is very thick.:dragonfly_The dragonflies are brightly coloured and fairly large. They stop and hover at various locations over the pond.:dragonflies_The dragonflies are brightly coloured and fairly large. They stop and hover at various locations over the pond.

[5] cellName: on a slope leading to the edge of the canyon.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a forested downward slope. To the East is a path through moss-covered rocks. To the West is is a heavily padlocked door.
[9] look: As you walk over to the edge of the plateau you can see over the canyon and to the beach in the distance.
[15] deeperLook: beach_The beach looks fairly small and enclosed. In the summer you can imagine it gets quite busy.

[5] cellName: on a path through moss covered rocks.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a deep thicket. To the West is a slope leading to the edge of the canyon. To the East is a grassy clearing. To the South is a rocky path.
[9] look: The path extends downwards to the south as it heads towards the beach.
[15] deeperLook: beach_The beach looks fairly small and enclosed. In the summer you can imagine it gets quite busy.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a path through brambles. To the West is a path through moss covered rocks. To the South is a rocky ledge.
[9] look: You look back up to the north and see how far you have travelled down already. You have to crane your neck a little to see Rifton village.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a path through moss covered rocks. To the East is a rocky ledge. To the South are hand-carved rock steps leading down.
[9] look: The path you are walking looks well-worn and the rock is smooth from years of use.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a grassy clearing. To the West is a rocky path. To the South is a rock-carved shrine.
[9] look: There is an old wooden bench facing the sea on the ledge. There is a metal plaque attached to it.
[15] deeperLook: bench_The bench is starting to rot in places and one or two planks of wood are missing.:sit_You take a well-deserved break to sit and stare at the sea for a while. When you stand up again you feel much more peaceful.:plaque_The plaque reads "In memory of Amy - from her grand daughter."

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a rocky path. To the East is a row of log benches. To the South is a thin passage between tall rock outcrops.
[9] look: The rocks are well worn but easy to walk along.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a rocky ledge. To the West are some hand-carved rocky steps.
[9] look: The shrine looks old and is covered in patches of lichen. A base of stone is topped with four carved columns that culminate in a flat roof. There is a bowl in the centre with a note next to it that reads "For the weary traveler".

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a series of steep ledges. To the South is the top of a waterfall.
[9] look: You are fairly close to the beach now and can smell the sea air.

[5] cellName: walking down a series of steep ledges.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a mossy rock clearing. To the East is a thin passage between tall rock outcrops.
[9] look: You watch your step as the path becomes slightly more perilous.

[5] cellName: walking down a thin passage between tall rock outcrops.
[8] gridDescription: To the North are hand-carved rock steps leading up. To the West is a series of steep ledges.
[9] look: The rocks tower above you as you continue down the rocky path.

[5] cellName: at the source of a waterfall.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a mossy rock clearing. To the South is a steep path beside the waterfall.
[9] look: You are standing at the source of a steep waterfall. There is a route down but you'll need to be cautious.:There is a waterfall here that has been diverted to the west due to a dam of heavy branches

[8] gridDescription: To the North is the top of a waterfall. To the South is Rifton Beach
[9] look: You are climbing carefully down a steep set of steps cut into the rock beside the waterfall.:You are climbing carefully down a steep set of steps cut into the rock. Beside you the rock has been worn smooth where a waterfall used to flow.

[5] cellName: at a dead end of the tunnel.
[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The river runs through a small crevice in the cave wall and out of sight to the west.

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: You are walking alongside an underground river. The cave walls are slimey to the touch.

[5] cellName: at a T-Junction of the tunnel.
[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The ground shallows towards an underground river running along the northern cave wall. The river is running slowly to the west.

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: There is a series of shallow ledges that lead upwards to the east. The river creates a series of small waterfalls as it travels over them.

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: On the northern cave wall a small river emerges from the rock and runs to the west.

[5] cellName: at a T-Junction of the tunnel.
[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: There are markings on the cave wall here - it looks like someone has written on them.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: You look closer and the text reads "Guto was here. Bart is a loser!".

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The tunnel continues in what seems like an endless way!

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: You stop to look at the rocks in the cave wall and think about how many millions of years ago it must have been that they were created.
[15] deeperLook: rock_The rock that makes up the cave is igneous and was formed millions of years ago when Rifton was situated on a volcanic island.

[5] cellName: at a dead end of the tunnel.
[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the West is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The cave opens out slightly into an open cavern. You look up and see hundreds of bats sleeping on the cave ceiling!
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: The bats are startled by the noise and a swarm of them fly out from the ceiling. You duck as they come close. They circle round and settle back on the cave ceiling.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The cave floor steepens to the north and leads deeper into the cave. Rudimentary stairs have been carved into the ground.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: There are rough stone ledges that resemble stairs leading upwards to the south. You watch your step on these as they are somewhat slippery.

[5] cellName: at a dead end of the tunnel.
[8] gridDescription: To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The chasm narrows into a small tunnel that is impassable.

[8] gridDescription: To the East is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The cave is fairly shallow here and you have to bend over to continue walking.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The ceiling of the cave is low here.

[5] cellName: at a T-Junction of the tunnel.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel. To the North is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: There is little light coming from any direction of the cave. You can faintly here small animals moving around in the distance.
[15] deeperLook: animals_It sounds like there may be a colony of bats living in these caves.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: You can hear water slowly dripping from the ceiling. There is light coming from the east.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel. To the South is an exit out of the cave.
[9] look: There is light coming from the south where the cave opens out. You can hear the sound of water coming from outside.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel. To the North is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: You can hear water slowly dripping from the ceiling. There is light coming from the west.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The floor slopes down to the east. The walls of the cave are striped with mineral veins that stand out dramatically in the low light.
[15] deeperLook: mineral_The vein contains large shining grey-white crystals. The rocks here appear to be limestone so you decide the veins are likely to be caclcite.:vein_The vein contains large shining grey-white crystals. The rocks here appear to be limestone so you decide the veins are likely to be caclcite.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The mineral veins from the west are larger here - some reaching almost a metre in width. You shine your torch over them and the crystals glimmer in the light.
[15] deeperLook: mineral_The vein contains large shining grey-white crystals. The rocks here appear to be limestone so you decide the veins are likely to be caclcite.:vein_The vein contains large shining grey-white crystals. The rocks here appear to be limestone so you decide the veins are likely to be caclcite.

[5] cellName: at the opening of a cave.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel. To the South is an open chasm.
[9] look: The tunnel to the west opens out into a large chasm. There are stalagmites reaching up from the ground and stalactites that almost meet them from above.
[15] deeperLook: stalagmite_The stalagmite is wet to the touch and is almost as tall as you. You remember reading that it can take up to 1000 years for every 10cm of growth.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the North is a dark tunnel. To the South is an open chasm.
[9] look: The walls of the chasm extend up high and you can see the slanted rock beds in thick grey layers.
[15] deeperLook: bed_The rock beds are fairly blocky and have a lot of fractures running through - common for limestone.:rock_The rock beds are fairly blocky and have a lot of fractures running through - common for limestone.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The cave ceiling is quite shallow here - mind your head!

[5] cellName: outside a cave - standing behind a waterfall.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a cave.
[9] look: You are looking out of a small exit of the cave. A large waterfall is cascading over the rocks in front of you. You can see past the water at the edges and can just about make out parts of Rifton village in the distance.
[15] deeperLook: waterfall_You decide it's best not to get too close to the water as it looks pretty powerful!

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the East is an open chasm.
[9] look: You walk carefully between dozens of large stalagmites. You can hear water dripping from above and wonder how long it took for these mineral structures to form.
[15] deeperLook: stalagmite_The stalagmite is wet to the touch and is almost as tall as you. You remember reading that it can take up to 1000 years for every 10cm of growth.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the West is an open chasm.
[9] look: You look closely at the flat smooth rock you are walking on and can see very small fossils.
[15] deeperLook: fossil_The small spirals you can see are indicative of ammonites. You can also see a few shells that may have belonged to other molluscs in the past.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: You can see a small tunnel leading off the main one you have been walking along. It looks like the cave is mainly natural in formation although you can see from rubble and markings on the wall that the walls have been excavated further than their original extent.
[15] deeperLook: rubble_The rocks on the floor contain large inclusions of green and black minerals.:markings_You can see where the tools the geologists have used have scraped along the walls of the cave.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The tunnel you are walking along is narrowing and becoming harder to walk along.

[5] cellName: at a dead end of the tunnel.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The tunnel is too narrow to continue walking through. You can see that it extends back into the cave further through a deep crack in the rock.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: You reach into the crack in the cave wall to see how far it goes...

[8] gridDescription: To the East is an open chasm. To the South is a glowing light.
[9] look: The cave is lighter here and you can see a faint glow coming from the south.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is an open chasm.
[9] look: The air in the cave smells a little different here.
[15] deeperLook: air_The air smells faintly of moss and stale water.:smell_The air smells faintly of moss and stale water.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is an open chasm. To the North is an open chasm.
[9] look: You walk towards the corner of the cave. There are a large amount of cracks in the wall that are likely home to a lot of small creatures.
[15] deeperLook: crack_Some of the cracks are filled with white crystals. It looks like when these formed the cracks were forced apart.:creatures_You take a closer look and see a few tiny spiders run in and out of the cracks.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the South is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: There is litle light left from the cave entrance and the tunnel seems to extend onwards for quite a way. You can faintly hear water drops falling behind you.

[5] cellName: in a dark tunnel illuminated by a glowing pool.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: You see a glowing pool of turquoise liquid in the floor of the cave. You suddenly feel thirsty...
[15] deeperLook: pool_The pool is fairly large and is surrounded by shallow rock ledges. The liquid is glowing faintly and highlights rocks in the cave wall in turquoise.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a dark tunnel. To the East is a dark tunnel.
[9] look: The cave entrance narrows to a passageway that turns sharply to the right.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a dark tunnel. To the East is an exit from the cave to Rifton Village.
[9] look: Light from outside illuminates the inside of the cave. There is moss growing on rocks near the entrance and you can hear water falling drop by drop into pools on the ground. You can't see very far ahead but a flashlight may help illumiate the path.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: The water in the pool looks fresh and cool. The igneous rocks in this cave are rich in minerals. This makes the water from Rifton Cave famous for its mineral content.
[15] deeperLook: moss_The moss is very prevelant and probably provides homes to a lot of life forms.

[5] cellName: standing in front of a tall cliff.
[8] gridDescription: To the East is a rock-pool. To the South is a steep sand dune.
[9] look: There is a powerful waterfall blocking your way to the East. It looks like you could get to the other side if the flow was weakened at its source back in the forest.:A waterfall used to run into the rock-pool to the East. Now there are rocky stepping stones across to the other side.

[5] cellName: climbing over a series of rock stepping stones in a rock-pool.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a tall cliff. To the East is a rock-pool.
[9] look: The rocks are large and fairly close together and you have no problem jumping between them.

[5] cellName: climbing over a series of rock stepping stones in a rock-pool.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a rock-pool. To the East is a rocky ledge.
[9] look: The rocks are smaller here and you have to be more careful when jumping between them.
[15] deeperLook: fall_You stumble and fall into the pool! Luckily it's not too deep and you are able to regain your balance and your dignity.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a rock-pool.
[9] look: In the cliff face something shimmers - could it be ellondite?

[5] cellName: walking across a steep sand dune.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a tall cliff. To the South is a patch of marram grass.
[9] look: Your feet slip as you take steps and you move slowly through the dune. You can see small shells littered throughout the sand.
[15] deeperLook: shell_You pick up a shell to look at. It is a pale pink colour and is no larger than your fingernail.:shells_You pick up a shell to look at. It is a pale pink colour and is no larger than your fingernail.

[5] cellName: walking over a steep sand dune.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a tall cliff. To the South is a patch of marram grass.
[9] look: You jump and slide down the dune - collecting a large amount of sand in your shoes along the way!
[15] deeperLook: sand_You stop to empty the sand from your shoes.

[8] gridDescription: To the East the beach continues for a while before it reaches the quay. To the South there is a muddy river trickling from the North.
[9] look: The hut has a straw-thatched roof and is situated in a rocky corner of the beach. A newspaper is open on the windowsill - its pages rustling in the slight breeze.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: The newspaper is open on a page with a headline about a sailors' strike.

[5] cellName: in a sandy patch of beach.
[8] gridDescription: To the West is a beach hut. To the East the beach ends abruptly at a wooden quay.
[9] look: You can feel that by now some of the sand has found its way into your shoes. A cliff towers above you to your north. The rock appears to be igneous in origin and has a dark gray colour.
[12] secondLevelLookDescription: You inspect the rock closely. It is made up of very small crystals that have a glassy appearence. From your geological studies you know that this means the lava that formed this rock cooled very quickly after eruption.

[8] gridDescription: The sea surrounds you on your North and South. To the West is a sandy beach. To the East the quay extends towards a large ferry.
[9] look: There is a sailor sitting on the edge of the quay. He is fishing in the ocean and looks peaceful.

[5] cellName: standing at the edge of a wooden quay.
[8] gridDescription: To the West the quay continues back to the beach. To the East is a large ferry.
[9] look: You look out across the sea and in the far distance you can see the mainland.

[5] cellName: walking through a patch of marram grass.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a steep sand dune. To the South is a shallow sand dune. To the East is the entrance to Rifton Forest.
[9] look: The grass scratches at your legs as you walk through it.
[15] deeperLook: grass_You take a closer look and find lots of small insects moving around at the roots of the grass.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a beach hut. To the East is the shore. To the South is a muddy estuary.
[9] look: The water is murky and you can't see the bottom of the river.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a sandy patch of the beach. To the West is a muddy river.
[9] look: You stare out to sea and try to glimpse the mainland.
[15] deeperLook: mainland_Before you moved to Rifton you used to live back on the mainland. Life is slower here and you're not sure if you prefer that yet or not.

[5] cellName: walking over a shallow sand dune.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a patch of marram grass. To the East is a series of small sand dunes. To the South is a patch of sandy beach.
[9] look: Your feet slip as you take steps and you move slowly through the dune.

[5] cellName: walking over a series of small sand dunes.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is the entrance to Rifton Forest. To the West is a shallow sand dune. To the East is the shore. To the South is a pebbly patch of beach.
[9] look: Your feet slip as you take steps and you move slowly through the dune. There is a worried looking group of teenagers talking amongst themselves.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is a series of small sand dunes. To the East is the shore.
[9] look: You stare out to sea and contemplae your life.
[15] deeperLook: life_What's it all about anyway?

[8] gridDescription: To the West is the shore. To the East is the shore.
[9] look: Directly opposite you to the North across a pool are some jagged rocks in the cliff face. Something is shimmering inside the cliff face - you wonder how you could get round there to investigate.:Directly opposite you to the North you can see jagged rocks that make up the cliff face.

[8] gridDescription: To the West is the shore. To the East is the shore.
[9] look: You hear noises from the east and see a large creature rampaging around the beach.:You stare out to the sea and try to glimpse the mainland.

[5] cellName: at the mouth of a muddy river.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a muddy river. To the West is the shore.
[9] look: You watch the river meet the water from the sea. The collision creates eddies and waves as the two liquids mix.

[5] cellName: on a sandy patch of beach.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a shallow sand dune. To the East is a pebbly patch of beach. To the South is a pebbly patch of beach.
[9] look: The sand is firm and much easier to walk on here. There are ripple marks from where the tide has been earlier.
[15] deeperLook: ripple_You've seen markings like this in rocks near Rifton. It's amazing to see the processes that form these at work in the present day!

[5] cellName: on a pebbly patch of beach.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a series of small sand dunes. To the West is a sandy patch of beach.
[9] look: You watch as the stones on the ground get covered by the tidal flow every few seconds and move slightly as the water retreats.

[5] cellName: on a pebbly patch of beach.
[8] gridDescription: To the North is a sandy patch of beach. To the South is the shore.
[9] look: The cliff walls come to an end to the west as the beach meets the sea.

[8] gridDescription: To the North is a pebbly patch of beach.
[9] look: You stare out to sea and think about your journey.
[15] deeperLook: journey_Your mission at the moment is exciting and you wonder where it will take you!
